The initial replacement of steppe-tundra or alpine meadows with wooded vegetation (mostly pinewoods and Corylus thickets) around Lago Verdarolo from around 14,700 to 13,700 cal BP (Figures 2, S2) was most likely a response to the rapid and abrupt warming at the onset of the Bølling/Allerød interstadial (+ 2.5—3 °C according to chironomid-based temperature reconstructions from the neighboring southern Alps (
